gRPC service design
Service name

Suggested:

WorkflowService
Main RPCs
Write path

These are for internal producers like cluster-controller, node-agent, and installer integration.

StartRun(StartRunRequest) returns (WorkflowRun)
UpdateRun(UpdateRunRequest) returns (google.protobuf.Empty)
FinishRun(FinishRunRequest) returns (google.protobuf.Empty)
RecordStep(RecordStepRequest) returns (WorkflowStep)
UpdateStep(UpdateStepRequest) returns (google.protobuf.Empty)
FailStep(FailStepRequest) returns (google.protobuf.Empty)
AddArtifactRef(AddArtifactRefRequest) returns (google.protobuf.Empty)
AppendEvent(AppendEventRequest) returns (google.protobuf.Empty)
Read path

These are for admin and AI.

GetRun(GetRunRequest) returns (WorkflowRunDetail)
ListRuns(ListRunsRequest) returns (ListRunsResponse)
GetRunEvents(GetRunEventsRequest) returns (GetRunEventsResponse)
GetCurrentRunsForNode(GetCurrentRunsForNodeRequest) returns (ListRunsResponse)
GetComponentHistory(GetComponentHistoryRequest) returns (ListRunsResponse)
GetWorkflowGraph(GetWorkflowGraphRequest) returns (WorkflowGraph)
Streaming path

Strongly recommended for admin live view.

WatchRun(WatchRunRequest) returns (stream WorkflowEventEnvelope)
WatchNodeRuns(WatchNodeRunsRequest) returns (stream WorkflowEventEnvelope)

This gives you a live reconciliation screen without polling madness.

