Actor-centered workflow representation

This is the most important part of the UI model.

We do not just want a flat step list.

We want the reconciliation process represented as a workflow with actor lanes, similar in spirit to a swimlane diagram:

cluster-controller
repository
node-agent
installer
runtime

That means each step should clearly indicate:

which actor owns it
which actor it hands off to next
whether the run is waiting, executing, blocked, failed, or completed at that handoff
Example: Scylla join/install workflow
Lane 1: cluster-controller
desired state detected
release evaluated
profile applicability checked
config rendered
package/version resolved
plan generated
plan written to node current plan slot
Lane 2: repository
artifact manifest selected
package resolved
checksum available
Lane 3: node-agent
plan observed
plan accepted
artifact download started
checksum verified
package extracted
installer selected
Lane 4: installer
spec detected
ensure dirs
install GPG key
install repo file
install OS packages
run post-install script
patch env/defaults
preserve controller config
readiness validation
Lane 5: runtime
systemd enable
systemd start/restart
port readiness
cluster join sanity
installed state publish
Back to cluster-controller
node state observed
release marked applied
workflow completed

That is the picture the admin should see.

